Added a FilterCommand class

lambdas within the FilterCommand class

describe the general case where no internships are
found in the Array list

new commands package.
Changed the way the setId(int index) function was called
in certain places to account for the proper numbering of
ID's when it is to be displayed to the user.
Changed the internships variable within the
InternshipList class from a static to a non-static member.
Otherwise, everytime a new InternshipList class is created,
the ArrayList of internships is reset and all data is lost.
Tested and ensured basic functionality of all the commands,
given the right input parameter lists.

the non static members in the
UpdateCommand class

commitResults.messageBody:
Changed the Command interface to an abstract class so as to facilitate the
sharing of common members such as INDEX_FIELD, INDEX_DATA and the
main internships list. Also, added a function so as to set from the main loop -
the common internship list for all commands to access, read and modify,

Deleted constructors within the subclass commands as they are instantiated
from the parent abstract class already. Changed the parameter type of the execute
function from String[] to ArrayList<String> so that we can call more functions
to easily manipulate the arguments that are passed into the function.

Gave a default id value for internships which haven't been instantiated yet.

Added a new file under the test folder just to showcase
how to operate the program and the expected behaviour/syntax.
Sample inputs and outputs only cover the basic cases without testing
too many edge cases.
made error handling for add command more comprehensive

Fixed bugs in DeleteCommand, FilterCommand,
SortCommand and Parser input to UpdateCommand

Fixed an issue because of which the list command
and help command did not work.
Fixed an issue related to the case where no input
is given after a command which requires additional
input.
